HEADWORD: Granulite
<hw>Gran"u*lite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Granule</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>A whitish, granular
rock, consisting of feldspar and quartz intimately mixed; -- sometimes
called <altname>whitestone</altname>, and
<altname>leptynite</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Granulose</ent>⟦br⟧
